description:
📍Am I Addicted @amiaddicted.sg 

Have you heard of this beautiful Pottery & Vegetarian Cafe nestled in Capitol?

This is the place to hang out with friends, family.
You can have pottery lessons and drink tea at the same time! So therapeutic and relaxing 😍

We tried

Jardin Bibimbap ($20)
🥗 Barley Rice mixed with carrots, spinach, capsicum, zucchini, bean sprouts and a poached egg with tasty Korean chilli paste. The quality of the ingredients they use are very good and fresh!  And brings out the taste of healthy Korean cuisine.

Hand Drip Coffee ($9)
☕️ Robust coffee Hand dripped by Oppa 😋

🫖 Antoninette!s Affair Lychee ($9)
Beautiful tea that comes in a whole flower blossom. Really like the Lychee and light tea flavour.

Drop by this lovely place to experience it 🥰

📍13 Stamford Road B2-51
Capitol Singapore
Studio (10am - 9pm) daily
Cafe (11am - 9pm) daily

Thank you @amiaddicted.sg for the invite.
.

I got Little J ‘s favourite Japanese Strawberries 🍓🍓 from @isetansg and they are so sweet and juicy ! Isetan is my to go supermarket whenever I am in Orchard!

I love their fresh and wide range of Japanese products! I love their vibrant Japanese culture there😍 

Isetan will celebrate its 50th anniversary this year. 
Isetan supermarket is well known for its fine and fresh Japanese food, there you could find Japanese food treasures. 
I always find my “ treasures there!” Foodstuffs that I used to find in Japan 

Isetan is known for these:
Vegetable
The seasonal fresh vegetable and fruis are brought by air 4 times a week.
Now it is a season of Fresh Strawberries! 🍓🍓

Egg
The Mangetsu pasteurized eggs are well loved for those who love the raw eggs. 
Japanese have a food culture to eat egg as raw such as Tamagokakw goban (literally just cup of rice topped on raw egg!) 

Wagyu
Wagyu are from Tochigi, Saga and Sendai from Japan. 
Wagyu is quite popular among Isetan customers. 

Rice
There are more than 20 kind of Japanese rice all the time. 
Japanese rice is good for making Sushi-rice. 

Sauce dressing 
Isetan has a wide range of Japanese sauce and dressing.
Pounzu, wasabi based and Japanese Worcestershire sauce etc 
You will never get bored to explore its collection!

Fish
There is a Japanese chef who takes care of preparing sashimi & sushi etc.
If you buy blocks of sashimi, you could ask chef to slice them as you like!

Tomiz Corner 
There is a corner of Japanese baking ingredients section by Tomiz.
Tomiz is well known as Tomizawa Shoten, a provider of all sort of baking ingredients. For baking lover like me ❤️

Visit https://www.instagram.com/isetansg/Supermarket
Sunday to Thursday & eve of public holidays, 10am – 9pm
Friday & Saturday, 10am – 9pm
Address 📍
350 Orchard Road
Shaw House
Singapore 238868
Tel: 65-6733 1111

Thank you @spoonful.sg and @isetansg for the supermarket tour invite 🌸

We found a Japanese Hawker hidden Gem! One of their outlets is in Hougang! So happy it’s near to me 😍

@ishirosg is a Japanese fusion Donburi concept that aims to captivate patrons with its unique  flavours & affordable dishes with healthy options too!

What we had:
🐠 Mentaiko Salmon Bowl $9.40
🐠Unagi Bowl $11.40
🍤 Friwd Tempura $6
💛 Chicken Karaage $6

I love Salmon Mentaiko and their bowl definitely met my expectations! It’s like good quality restaurant in a hawker setting. The onsen egg that comes with it is also cooked perfectly! 
The same goes for the unagi bowl with it’s generous portions and juicy flesh, again perfect with the onsen egg. They also use good pearl 🍚 

I would definitely recommend anyone looking for good quality Japanese food at affordable prices! They have a few outlets, so check them out 💛

Special thanks to @laoniangagency for the kind invite🙏 and @ishirosg for the delicious food and hospitality.

【Fu Lin Bar & Kitchen 】
Nestled in the heart of the city, Fu Lin Bar & Kitchen serves up its famous Fried Yong Tofu during the day, coated in a unique meat gravy made with their original recipe since 1995. 
At night, the restaurant transforms itself into a modern Chinese local street bar with hip ambience and trendy industrial-style decor. 

Painstakingly created after rounds of experimentation and elimination, their 🆕
curated dinner menu boasts a combination of local fare, Sichuan bar bites, specialty alcohols AND more that you can enjoy with their signature Fried Yong Tofu.

👄Featured some of their signature Bar dishes:
◾️💋Mala Fish
◾️💋XO Carrot Cakes
◾️💋Iberico Pork
◾️Baby Back Ribs
◾️Mochi

We really enjoyed their fried XO carrot cakes, spicy shiok Mala fish & tender yummy Iberico pork Plus the unique old school taste Mochi 🤤..

description:
Made a simple scallop with cabbage soup for dinner tonight using Aomori Scallop 3S.
These sweet and succulent scallops from Japan (Aomori) are ideal as soup stock.
Love their firm flesh texture and natural sweetness. 😍😋
Will try pan-frying next.
The best part, these scallops are halal certified. 👍

Check out @sakana.sg or go to their website at www.sakanasg.com to place your order. 
They specialise in premium, sustainable Japanese seafood.

Special thanks to @mutsu_japan for this opportunity to try this bag of scallop.

Discovered a hip cafe near Haji Lane @afterwitsg - a great place to catch up with friends after work or during the weekend when you are around the ‘hood. 
This halal chillax and cozy cafe serves up pretty authentic Mexican fare and bites.

What we had:

Appetiser:

~ Classy Nachos ($15.90)
Chicken 🐓 with melted cheese 🧀, home-made guacamole, Pico De Gallo and corn.
One can never go wrong with some classy nachos. Always a great start as an appetiser to share. 👍

Mains:

~ Pizzamasa ($18.90) 🍕 
A 12" crisp tortilla base topped with beef chorizo, cheddar 🧀 Parmesan Salsa Roja and Pico De Gallo 
A super flavourful 🍕- perfect for sharing! 😍👍

~ Shank You ($27)
A 24-hour slow cooked lamb shank 🐑 with spicy roasted baby potatoes 🥔, Pepita and Cilantro Gremolata in Tangy Olive Oil.
A succulent, tender and flavourful lamb 🐑 shank dish. What more to say… 😋

Gotta end our meal with sweet treat:

~ Churros ($10.90)
Coated in Cinnamon Sugar with Chocolate 🍫 Sauce. 
Freshly made with crispy and crunchy exterior yet light and airy on the inside! 
So good on its own or dip it in the chocolate sauce for the extra sweetness! 🥰❤️

Refreshing summery concoctions 🍹:

~ Sunrise in Tulum ($8.90) 
A drink consists of Pina Coco, wildberry, lime juice and sun orange in soda water with mint 

~ Earl Grey Cold Brew ($5.50)

~ Laying on Your Coconut 🥥 ($8.90) 
Coconut Water, Pina Coco with lime juice and basil

We were so stuffed at the end of this meal that we needed a long walk to digest all the yummies we just had… 🤣🤪
Perfect weather today too, so thankful for that.

Remember to refuel for another great week ahead, peeps! 
Sunday Funday! 🙌😎

description:
Slow down and enjoy the simple pleasures in life… 
So here I am again, savouring my sweet treats from @chowzanplq1

All thanks to @mcdlalaland’s post the other day, I decided to order their D24 Durian Boost ($7.90)!
😱🤯 Oh boy… This is a definite MUST order dessert for durian lover! 🙌
Loved this dollop of smooth, thick and buttery durian purée/flesh with a balanced flavour profile that's sweet with notes of bitter. 
I can eat this everyday! 😍😋

For mango 🥭 lovers, go for Mango Sago Konjac Pearl & Vanilla Ice Cream ($7.50).
This is such a refreshing dessert with juicy chunks of mango and chewy Konjac jelly.  The additional scoop of vanilla ice cream 🍨 just round this all up to make this a satisfying sweet treat indeed. 😃👍

Life is good especially on a Friday! 🙌🌈

Tasty Raining Monday!🌧🌧
Spicy 🥵 & Indulgent to keep you warm and cozy!!👍🥰 

One of the many comfort food that I go for when my day's been less than ideal. Amy Stew( Budae Jjigae) in a claypot 🍲is a solid meal overall. It is Korean hot pot loaded with Kimchi, spam, different kind of mushrooms🍄🍄, sausages, lettuce 🥬, pork belly & pork collar🥓🥓, tteokbokki, tofu, ramen 🍜, cheese 🧀, onion 🧅 and much more!

Well, great company is even better 😀😀We slurp till the very last drop, shiok!😋😋
Warning:⚠️⚠️ A pot of addictive and high calories food!!💕💕

Simply easy to make this pot of goodness. 

🌟Mix 4Tbsp Korean chili flakes (Gochugaru), 4 Tbsp mirin, 2Tbsp soy sauce, 2Tbsp minced garlic, 1Tbsp sugar, 3Tbsp Korean chili paste (Gochujang)and a few sprinkles of ground black pepper in small bowl. You can adjust based on your preferance for the sauce.

🌟All you need is to assemble the ingredients including the sauce (except for instant ramen noodles, rice cakes, chopped chilies 🌶 & green onion and cheese 🧀) in the pot. 

🌟Pour in homemade 1.5litre chicken stock and let it boil for about 10 mins. Once boil, add it instant ramen noodles, rice cakes, green onion and cheese to cook for about 2 mins. Lower heat if you are using portable burner and Enjoy! We cooked in a claypot  to keep the food warm while enjoying on dining table.

I don’t go long without eating. I never starve myself. 🤭🤭I try to grab a healthy snack if possible. 😅😅Make snacking less sinful with Kokkal corn 🌽 snacks.

They are available in 3️⃣ flavours: Original, Sweet & Sour and Grilled Corn. It is pretty to cool to cap corn snacks onto your fingers like little hats🎩. Then, eating them off one by one. 🤟😽

Super delicious 😋, airy and crunchy. I promise you can’t stop at one. 🤭🤭

Another Korean’s favourite 😻 snack is the ABC Chocolate 🍫 Cookie 🍪. Sweet refreshing creamy chocolate 🍫 and soft cookie 🍪. Always the ultimate combination!! 😜😜 There are available in 3️⃣ flavours: original, cookies & cream and mint 🌱. 

The seasonal mint ABC Chocolate 🍫 Cookie only available at @shopee_sg Supermarket, @candyempire and Eccelente by @haomartsg . Kids 🧒👦👧 will love them too as they can do some colouring from inside the box while enjoying the bite-sized snack. Prefect to keep your kids time occupied. 🤣🤣

Do check out @lottesweetworldsg when comes to great snack for carrying around to have it anytime. 👍👍Start stocking up those addictive snacks at @giantsingapore @shengsiongsupermarket_official @haomartsg @candyempire and U Star Minimart. Better still you can get them online through @redmartbylazada @shopee_sg supermarket and PandaNow.

Who love to munch them too? 🙋‍♀️🙋🙋🏼‍♂️

⭐️Matcha 🍵 Mont Blanc -Intense earthiness matcha taste provides the prefect contrast to the sweetness of chestnut mousse. Work wonder on the eye of matcha lover.☺️

- Light and creamy strawberry 🍓 chantilly cream beautifully stages on top of baked pistachio frangipane in crunchy tart shell. Decorated with strawberry macarons at the side. Chewy jam sandwiched between crisp exterior macarons.

BRDL Restaurant & Bar offer ively dishes featuring Asian flavours and exciting drinks at a chic yet relaxing ambience.

Recently they curated Restaurant Week Menu, which is only available from 4 to 27 March.

You can enjoy an incredible dining experience starting from $38 for lunch and $58 for dinner.

Featuring: Dinner Set SG$58++/Pax

Welcome Snack
Daily rotation of surprises from the kitchen

1st Course
Foie Gras & Duck Leg Terrine - Strawberries / Brioche / Balsamic
OR
Mussel Chowder Blue - Lip Mussel / XO Sauce

2nd Course
Green Curry Barramundi - Green Curry Pea Puree / Tom Kah / Compressed Green Mango
OR
Roasted Cod - Ginger & Soy Veloute / Fish Maw / Preserved Cabbage Salad

Herb Crusted Lamb Rack - Raspberry Puree / Lemon Verbena & Hazelnut Crust / Smoked Lamb Jus

It was a wonderful dining experience. Each dish looks exquisite, and the portion and taste are good. I think both desserts is mind-blow creation. I prefer this version of Mango Sticky Rice over the original one! The Durian Cheesecake is made with Musang King Durian. 🇸🇬 Delicious and fun hot pot restaurant! Open until 3 am!

The famous Qi Xiang Chicken Pot in Kovan opened a flagship hotpot outlet on the 3rd floor of The Chevrons with extended opening hours till 3 am daily and a nice ambience. 

Their soup base is made in-house and selling at $11.90 for half-pot (Choose from pumpkin, sauerkraut, herbs, tom yum, laksa, collagen soup and mala tang)

Just add $5 per person for all you can eat side dishes, Chinese tea, lime juice, fruit, ice cream and 15 condiments. 

Recently they have launched a new all-day breakfast (You can order during evening or midnight)
+Chicken Chop $9.90 - Chicken Chop is seasoned and inspired by suggestions from Dr Leslie Tay (ieatishootipost).
+Rosti Plate $10.90 - Chef has experience in western food. The scrambled egg is very creamy and smooth. Served with Rosti and sausage, it is even cheaper than Cafe.

Special dishes:
+XO Carrot Cake $10.90 (Must try, highly recommended! There are so many things on the table, and this is the first dish we finish)
+Szechuan Smoked Duck Breast $18.90 - They spent nearly 9 Months on R&D
+Egg Fried Rice $3 - It looks ordinary, but the taste is strong with Wok Hei.
+Oyster Omelette (Orh Luak) $10.90

Why do I say it's fun? Because here you can also use the secret code to get some freebie!

1️⃣ 大吉大利，我要吃鸡 Dàjí dàlì, wǒ yào chī jī 
Receive a free chicken cutlet - It's a bit like Taiwanese fried chicken chop, and they use fried chicken thighs. It's big and tender, with some mala flavour, very addicting.

2️⃣ Gentlemen:我是小鲜肉 OR Ladies:我是小仙女，我要吃小鲜肉  Wǒ shì xiǎo xiānnǚ，Wǒ yào chī xiǎo xiān ròu
Receive free pork belly and pork collar platter

3️⃣ Sing the song 泡沫 (Pào mò) by GEM or Super Idol 的笑容 都没你的甜 chorus 
To get a cup of bubble tea!

4️⃣ If you are celebrating a friend's birthday, remember to make a reservation and tell them. The birthday boy/girl will receive an ice cream banana and noodles for free.

🎉Limited time offer🎉

Free 2 Soup base when you spend over $100
Maximum 2 soup base orders per table.

description:
[SWIPE ▶️] Are you having a rough day? Eat ramen!! 🍜@ramenkingsg is opened by Chef Simon Song, who is formerly from Ramen Santouka. Ramen can be found everywhere but can you find affordable ramen which is just as good? 🥺
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I have tried the Tonkotsu ramen ($8) and Kurobuta Toroniku Spicy Miso ramen ($15). Their ramen prices range from $8 - $9.50 with the exception of the Kurobuta Toroniku ones.
Their ramen here is the kind of restaurant standard and the broth is rich. The tonkotsu one has that kind of rich and milky consistency, whereas the miso one has a savory one with a slight fiery kick. The charsiew for the tonkotsu is on the thinner side but the kurobuta one was tender and nice. 
I really enjoyed slurping the ramen! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
They have gyoza and cheese gyoza as sides.
📍 Blk 829 Tampines St 81
📍 Canberra Plaza #01-07 (After 10 March)

description:
Whipped up a hearty bowl of 🍅 Tomato Ramen 🍜 using Singapore’s first ever cooked Ramen from @kangkangnoodles ! 

The fresh pasteurised Ramen is higher in protein and lower in sodium comparing to the other cooked oriental noodles in the market. 👍🏼 

Added some simple ingredients like Egg Tofu, Luncheon Meat, Enoki Mushrooms, Ramen Egg (cook in boiling water for 6 minutes and put in ice water after), some Fried Garlic, chopped Spring Onions and a packet of ready-to-cook Tomato broth! 🤩 

And most importantly, it is super easy and convenient to prepare the Ramen, just parboil the ramen in boiling water for 30 seconds, topped it up with the broth and other cooked ingredients, and a hearty bowl of Tomato Ramen is ready within minutes! Love the soft & springy texture of the Ramen, and it goes so well with the tangy tomato broth! 🥰 

Try out my simple yet yummy & nutritious recipe or have fun creating your own recipes with @kangkangnoodles Ramen today! 😉 
-
❤️ @getkobe

🏷 #Kangkangnoodles #Kangkangramen #sghomecooking

What’s your comfort food? Curry rice is definitely one of mine! 🥰 

🍛 @legendscissorscut_curryrice 

Featured on 8 DAYS Eat & Miss Tam Chiak, started by a veteran Ex-Santi Chef that made it viral for their famous Scissorscut Curry Rice! 🤩 

With a wide variety of dishes to choose from, there’s also preset combos for the indecisive diners. 

🍛 Set D (Chicken/Pork Chop + Braised Pork + Cabbage + Egg) for $5

📝 This combo is super value for money and really tasty! 👍🏼 

🍤 Crispy Prawn Fritters

📝 Also known as Pong Pong Prawn Fritters, it’s my childhood favourite, so nostalgic! ❤️ 

⭐️ I’ve actually ordered from them a few times via food delivery platforms prior to visiting their physical stall. I personally prefer it delivered as the rice will have soaked up the flavours from the curry gravy along the journey! It’s up to your personal preference though. 😉 

📍Blk 732 Yishun Ave 5, Singapore 760732

🚇 8-10 minutes walk from Exit D of 🔴 Yishun MRT Station 

🕒 Daily, 10.30am-7.30pm

⚠️ Do head over early as possible to avoid disappointment, just in case they are sold out for the day before their closing time! 

🙏 Special thanks to @laoniangagency for arranging, @legendscissorscut_curryrice for the invite!
